,\"id\":\"1367480922241654786\",\"source\":\"Twitter for iPhone\",\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":0,\"reply_count\":0,\"like_count\":0,\"quote_count\":0},\"text\":\"Unfortunately there is no recorded observation of C. glomerata in HK. So I really can’t be sure.\",\"author_id\":\"7820042\",\"created_at\":\"2021-03-04T14:23:53.000Z\",\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1367480920689700864\"}],\"conversation_id\":\"1367480920689700864\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"id\":\"1367480920689700864\",\"source\":\"Twitter for iPhone\",\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":0,\"reply_count\":1,\"like_count\":0,\"quote_count\":0},\"text\":\"https://t.co/gRnjO238C1\\nSo I got home to find one of our Pieris rapae caterpillars being parasitized. A quick search on the Internet reveals that Cotesia glomerata is a parasitoid wasp that targets P. rapae.\",\"author_id\":\"7820042\",\"entities\":{\"urls\":[{\"start\":0,\"end\":23,\"url\":\"https://t.co/gRnjO238C1\",\"expanded_url\":\"http://www.inaturalist.org/observations/70552854\",\"display_url\":\"inaturalist.org/observations/7…\",\"images\":[{\"url\":\"https://pbs.twimg.com/news_img/1367480925357936641/pQq9HNOY?format=jpg&name=orig\",\"width\":1024,\"height\":576},{\"url\":\"https://pbs.twimg.com/news_img/1367480925357936641/pQq9HNOY?format=jpg&name=150x150\",\"width\":150,\"height\":150}],\"status\":200,\"title\":\"Insects (Class Insecta) observed by Kal Sze\",\"description\":\"Insects from Yau Ma Hom Road, Kwai Chung, New Territories, HK on March 04, 2021 at 09:33 PM by Kal Sze. I’m most interested in the parasites on this Pieris caterpillar. Here is a video of them wriggli...\",\"unwound_url\":\"https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/70552854\"}]},\"created_at\":\"2021-03-04T14:23:52.000Z\",\"conversation_id\":\"1367480920689700864\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"id\":\"1367354738795155456\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"entities\":{\"hashtags\":[{\"start\":9,\